name: Wen Ji Noodle 文记面食

reviews.text:
Chance upon this stall sell various type of noodle in the coffeeshop opposite Serangoon sports Complex. This was my second visit, the first time when I was here, they were already closed. Apart from Lor mee, they also sell fishball noodle, mee rubus and laksa. Over here, they have the normal lor mee as well as the signature lor mee, both are SGD$4 and $5 respectively. The difference is the type ingredient the lor mee has.

Ordered their signature lor mee, which comes with fried fish fillet, fried wanton, nor hiang as pork belly. I was given fishcake as substitute since i opted out the pork belly. Gravy was flavorful and  has a distinctive herbal taste. Besides that, the gravy has a nice consistency.

Overall, i enjoyed the bowl of lor mee, and would come back again to eat. There is also a popular roast meat joint in the same coffeeshop.

Very nice fish ball noodles. Traditional style with tasty fish ball soup. Aunty remember customer very well and friendly. Pop by here n grab a taste of their fishball noodle. Oh....please come early in the morning n be nice n queue up properly yeah.......

Friendly staff
Lor mee overall not bad
Opts for $6 fried fish lor mee
Short queues for it cos prepared by lady boss
Worth the wait

Decent bowl of Lor Mee. Ordered a signature lor mee that gives me fried fish pieces. Added more vinegar on my own.
Overall, the bowl is full of flavours.

Mediocre lor mee
$4.50 for normal and $5.50 for fish fritter
